    <h2 class="section-title">At the Edge of Time</h2>
    <p>Things get weird when flying across time zones. When flying west, it feels like time is slowing down. And when flying east, it feels like time is speeding up.</p>
    <p>At the edge between two time zones, it’s possible to arrive at your destination at an earlier local time than you took off. Let’s have a look at Chicago and Detroit.</p>
  </div>
